959
01:34:57,316 --> 01:35:01,278
Lex, what has chewing gum got to do
with the secrets of the universe?

960
01:35:01,987 --> 01:35:03,614
[SIGHS]

961
01:35:04,364 --> 01:35:06,450
Right. Right, Miss Teschmacher.

962
01:35:06,617 --> 01:35:07,701
[SIGHS]

963
01:35:09,494 --> 01:35:11,496
N, N, N...

964
01:35:11,663 --> 01:35:14,374
M. You want M, Mr. Luthor?
Coming right up.

965
01:35:15,792 --> 01:35:17,502
So there you go. M.

966
01:35:17,669 --> 01:35:20,380
M, as in "moron," Otis?
No, no, no. It's N!

967
01:35:20,589 --> 01:35:23,842
N, as in "Neanderthal,"
"nincompoop," "nitwit."

968
01:35:24,009 --> 01:35:26,887
- And L, as in “ladder"!
- Ladder, Mr. Luthor. Coming right up.

969
01:35:27,095 --> 01:35:29,473
I didn't see, because I...

970
01:35:29,640 --> 01:35:32,517
I'm sorry, Mr. Luthor. I-- Ooh!

971
01:35:32,684 --> 01:35:36,897
In the interview, he says that
the planet Krypton...

972
01:35:37,814 --> 01:35:40,567
...exploded in 1948.

973
01:35:40,734 --> 01:35:45,739
Ridiculous little freak took three years
in a rocket ship to get to Earth.

974
01:35:45,906 --> 01:35:51,370
- Ergo...
- Ergo. Ergo, 1948, three years...

975
01:35:51,536 --> 01:35:52,913
He's 6'4", you know that?

976
01:35:53,121 --> 01:35:56,750
Do you know why the number 200
is so vitally descriptive...

977
01:35:56,917 --> 01:35:59,711
...to both you and me?
It's your weight and my IQ.

978
01:35:59,878 --> 01:36:02,130
Now, think, people, think.

979
01:36:03,006 --> 01:36:05,759
Deductive reasoning,
that's the name of the game.

980
01:36:07,928 --> 01:36:12,391
Fragments from the planet Krypton
exploded and went into outer space.

981
01:36:12,557 --> 01:36:16,603
It is reasonable to assume
that some of those particles of debris...

982
01:36:16,770 --> 01:36:18,647
...drifted to Earth.

983
01:36:20,524 --> 01:36:21,566
Meteorites.

984
01:36:22,025 --> 01:36:23,568
[SPEAKS GERMAN]

985
01:36:24,778 --> 01:36:26,780
Voilà!

986
01:36:31,785 --> 01:36:32,953
Voilà.

987
01:36:33,161 --> 01:36:35,289
Voilà.

988
01:36:36,957 --> 01:36:39,751
A meteorite found in Addis Ababa?

989
01:36:39,918 --> 01:36:44,881
Uh, I know I'm gonna get rapped
in the mouth for this, but so what?

990
01:36:45,048 --> 01:36:48,802
So what? You mean, to us
they are just meteorites.

991
01:36:48,969 --> 01:36:53,932
Fair enough. But the level
of specific radioactivity is so high...

992
01:36:54,099 --> 01:36:57,686
...to anyone from the planet Krypton,
this substance is lethal.

993
01:36:58,478 --> 01:37:00,314
Wait a minute, Mr. Luthor.

994
01:37:00,480 --> 01:37:04,609
You mean fire and bullets
can't hurt this guy, but this stuff here...

995
01:37:04,776 --> 01:37:07,112
ALL:
Will kill him.

996
01:37:07,279 --> 01:37:08,655
- Oh.
- Oh.

997
01:37:08,822 --> 01:37:10,324
Yeah, wow...

998
01:37:10,490 --> 01:37:12,242
Doesn't it give you kind of a...

999
01:37:12,409 --> 01:37:16,496
...a shudder of electricity through you
to be in the same room with me?

1000
01:37:17,706 --> 01:37:20,751
Not like the one you'll get
when you try to lay that rock on him.

1001
01:37:20,917 --> 01:37:24,171
He can see you coming from miles
with those super peepers of his.

1002
01:37:24,338 --> 01:37:28,258
Oh, Lord, you gave them eyes,
but they cannot see.

1003
01:37:28,425 --> 01:37:30,761
Nor can Superman, through lead.

1004
01:37:32,512 --> 01:37:35,182
He can't see through lead.

1005
01:37:35,349 --> 01:37:37,517
And kryptonite will destroy him.

1006
01:37:40,937 --> 01:37:42,814
- Any questions, class?
- Wow.

1007
01:37:43,857 --> 01:37:46,360
Wonder what they're wearing
in Addis Ababa.

1008
01:37:46,526 --> 01:37:50,197
- Looks like a burnoose, a wraparound.
TESCHMACHER: There's gold, 24 karat...

1009
01:37:50,364 --> 01:37:53,742
OTIS: Are we going to Addis Ababa?
- ...not 18 karat gold.

1010
01:37:54,034 --> 01:37:56,536
<i>Mother Bird to missile convoy. Over.</i>

1011
01:37:56,745 --> 01:37:59,206
<i>MAN:
Missile convoy to Mother Bird, go ahead.</i>

1012
01:37:59,373 --> 01:38:02,167
<i>Everything looks good. See you at base.</i>

1013
01:38:02,334 --> 01:38:06,505
<i>- Over and out.
- Roger, Mother Bird. Over and out.</i>

1014
01:38:13,345 --> 01:38:15,472
[BEEPING]

1015
01:38:19,393 --> 01:38:21,186
[TIRES SCREECH]

1016
01:38:49,589 --> 01:38:53,343
MAN 1: Man, look at this.
MAN 2: Whoo-wee. Looks pretty bad.

1017
01:38:55,679 --> 01:38:59,099
MAN 3: Think she's dead?
MAN 4: Better check her pulse.

1018
01:39:08,942 --> 01:39:10,777
All right, get an ambulance down here.

1019
01:39:10,944 --> 01:39:13,613
I don't wanna hold this convoy up
more than I have to.

1020
01:39:14,114 --> 01:39:16,867
She's having trouble breathing, sir.
What do you think?

1021
01:39:17,033 --> 01:39:19,453
Well, I suggest
vigorous chest massage.

1022
01:39:19,619 --> 01:39:22,289
If that doesn't work, mouth-to-mouth.

1023
01:39:22,456 --> 01:39:23,915
Yes, sir.

1024
01:39:24,082 --> 01:39:27,627
Sergeant, I won't have one of my men
doing anything I wouldn't do myself.

1025
01:39:27,836 --> 01:39:29,921
- Yeah, but, sir--
- Get an ambulance.

1026
01:39:30,088 --> 01:39:32,090
All right, men. Gather around.

1027
01:39:32,841 --> 01:39:34,885
About face!

1028
01:39:48,106 --> 01:39:49,858
[SIREN APPROACHES]

1029
01:40:02,078 --> 01:40:03,497
Hi.

1030
01:40:03,747 --> 01:40:05,081
Somebody hurt?

1031
01:40:19,638 --> 01:40:20,972
Ah.

1032
01:40:21,139 --> 01:40:25,519
I did it. I did it, Mr. Luthor,
Miss Teschmacher.

1033
01:40:25,685 --> 01:40:28,980
- I did it, just like you told me.
- All right, Otis. All right.

1034
01:40:29,147 --> 01:40:32,984
All right, Otis. Listen,
it isn't that I don't trust you, but...

1035
01:40:33,151 --> 01:40:35,529
I don't trust you, Otis.
What did you do?

1036
01:40:35,695 --> 01:40:38,949
Well, I-- I set the first...

1037
01:40:39,115 --> 01:40:42,160
...directional vector to 38...

1038
01:40:42,327 --> 01:40:46,373
...the second one to 67,
and the third one to 117.

1039
01:40:46,540 --> 01:40:49,626
- What about the fourth one?
- What fourth one?

1040
01:40:49,793 --> 01:40:53,046
Now, wait a minute. Wait a minute.
The third one to 117?

1041
01:40:53,213 --> 01:40:55,632
Yes. See? I wrote it down, Mr. Luthor.
I wrote it--

1042
01:40:55,799 --> 01:40:57,968
Otis. Otis!

1043
01:40:58,134 --> 01:41:01,805
The third one was supposed to be 11,
and the fourth one, seven.

1044
01:41:01,972 --> 01:41:05,684
Oh. Well, gee, Mr. Luthor.

1045
01:41:05,850 --> 01:41:08,395
Oh, I see. I guess my arm
wasn't long enough, see?

1046
01:41:08,562 --> 01:41:11,147
Otis, would you like to see a long arm?

1047
01:41:11,314 --> 01:41:14,192
Otis, would you like to see
a very, very long arm?

1048
01:41:14,359 --> 01:41:17,571
- Oh, no, Mr. Luthor.
- Otis. Otis!

1049
01:41:17,737 --> 01:41:18,989
Ah!

1050
01:41:26,204 --> 01:41:28,248
[HONKING]

1051
01:41:28,498 --> 01:41:29,749
[SIREN WAILS]

1052
01:41:29,958 --> 01:41:33,712
- All right, get it right, will you?
- Yes, Mr. Luthor.

1053
01:41:36,172 --> 01:41:38,842
McDonald, I thought you told me
this road was blocked off.

1054
01:41:39,009 --> 01:41:42,387
- Jablonski, you said it was blocked.
- I didn't ask him, I asked you.

1055
01:41:43,597 --> 01:41:46,224
All right, follow me. Follow me, men.

1056
01:41:46,975 --> 01:41:50,270
- Back that thing off the road.
- Back that thing up out of here.

1057
01:41:53,690 --> 01:41:56,526
You fellas get back into that thing
and back it off the road.

1058
01:41:56,693 --> 01:41:58,903
We got a convoy coming through here.

1059
01:42:00,488 --> 01:42:03,617
Listen, you're gonna have to circle back.
I don't have time to argue.

1060
01:42:03,783 --> 01:42:05,368
Heck of a day, isn't it?

1061
01:42:08,496 --> 01:42:12,626
LEX: We took the wrong turn.
We were looking for Route 12.

1062
01:42:12,792 --> 01:42:16,296
- Route 12? That's back there, isn't it?
- No, sir. It's up there.

1063
01:42:18,214 --> 01:42:22,010
- Sergeant, we took the wrong route.
- I'm a lieutenant, a naval officer.

1064
01:42:29,267 --> 01:42:30,894
Shut up!

1065
01:42:31,061 --> 01:42:32,812
Route 12 is back that way.

1066
01:42:39,402 --> 01:42:41,154
This man is a diabetic.

1067
01:42:51,831 --> 01:42:54,417
LOIS: As you know, my newspaper,
the <i>Daily Planet...</i>

1068
01:42:54,584 --> 01:42:58,004
...is very interested in that dam,
but what I don't understand...

1069
01:42:58,171 --> 01:43:00,757
...is why you'd sell out
to a person you've never met.

1070
01:43:00,924 --> 01:43:03,176
I mean, you don't even
know his name. Oh, yeah.

1071
01:43:06,096 --> 01:43:08,848
MAN:
At the stupid-high price he offered...

1072
01:43:09,057 --> 01:43:13,687
...for this worthless piece of desert,
I hope it's Custer.

1073
01:43:15,355 --> 01:43:18,024
Perfect.
That's just what I need, thank you.

1074
01:43:18,191 --> 01:43:22,612
<i>Reporting live from the launch site,
ground zero.</i>

1075
01:43:22,987 --> 01:43:26,116
<i>Well, today marks an historic occasion.</i>

1076
01:43:26,282 --> 01:43:31,371
<i>Two XK 101 rockets
will be launched simultaneously...</i>

1077
01:43:31,579 --> 01:43:34,207
<i>...one by the Army and by the Navy.</i>

1078
01:43:34,374 --> 01:43:36,710
Hi, everybody. Has anybody
seen Lois around today?

1079
01:43:36,876 --> 01:43:39,045
GIL: No, I haven't, but the chief
wants to see you.

1080
01:43:39,212 --> 01:43:41,631
You're blocking the set, Clark.

1081
01:43:41,798 --> 01:43:45,719
Sorry, Gil. How's Judy today, okay?
Good? Great.

1082
01:43:45,885 --> 01:43:47,679
- Excuse me, Mr. White?
- Come in, Kent.

1083
01:43:47,846 --> 01:43:50,724
You wanted to see me?
Sir, have you seen Lois anywhere today?

1084
01:43:51,599 --> 01:43:53,893
She's out west looking into
a land fraud deal.

1085
01:43:54,144 --> 01:43:56,730
Sent young Olsen with her
on his first assignment.

1086
01:43:56,896 --> 01:44:00,066
Some unidentified clown out there
is buying up thousands of acres...

1087
01:44:00,233 --> 01:44:02,569
...of worthless desert
at incredible prices.

1088
01:44:02,736 --> 01:44:04,320
That doesn't seem to make sense.

1089
01:44:04,487 --> 01:44:07,323
The world doesn't make sense.
You ought to know that by now.

1090
01:44:07,490 --> 01:44:09,826
Look at this dispatch
from Addis Ababa.

1091
01:44:09,993 --> 01:44:12,996
People break into a museum
at night, kill two people...

1092
01:44:13,163 --> 01:44:15,832
...and what do they take?
A worthless piece of meteorite.

1093
01:44:15,999 --> 01:44:17,542
- How do you figure that?
- Well...

1094
01:44:17,709 --> 01:44:20,920
...frankly, I've never been able
to understand violence in any form.

1095
01:44:21,129 --> 01:44:25,216
I know that about you, Kent. That's one
of the reasons I wanted to talk to you.

1096
01:44:25,633 --> 01:44:29,012
I've been in this news game 40 years,
man and boy.

1097
01:44:29,179 --> 01:44:32,515
And I got where I am
with guts, compassion...

1098
01:44:32,682 --> 01:44:36,436
...elbow grease and something
you're sadly lacking in, son.

1099
01:44:36,686 --> 01:44:38,772
- Humility?
- No, not humility.

1100
01:44:38,938 --> 01:44:40,732
You got bags of humility.

1101
01:44:40,899 --> 01:44:43,359
Aggression, confidence,
that's the ticket.

1102
01:44:43,526 --> 01:44:45,445
Take charge. Let people know
who you are.

1103
01:44:45,695 --> 01:44:47,155
[HIGH-PITCHED FREQUENCY]

1104
01:44:47,363 --> 01:44:49,240
[DOGS BARKING]

1105
01:44:54,037 --> 01:44:56,122
LEX [OVER FREQUENCY]: <i>This</i> is Lex <i>Luthor.</i>

1106
01:44:56,289 --> 01:45:01,085
<i>Only one thing with less than four legs
can hear this frequency, Superman: You.</i>

1107
01:45:01,461 --> 01:45:03,880
<i>In approximately five minutes,
a poison gas pellet...</i>

1108
01:45:04,047 --> 01:45:06,758
<i>...containing propane-lithium
compound...</i>

1109
01:45:06,925 --> 01:45:09,719
<i>...will be released through
the city's air ducts...</i>

1110
01:45:09,886 --> 01:45:13,223
<i>...effectively annihilating
half the population of Metropolis.</i>

1111
01:45:13,389 --> 01:45:16,768
I was a reporter before
most of my friends were copy boys.

1112
01:45:16,935 --> 01:45:19,771
I want you to do that.
Get Lois to introduce you to Superman.

1113
01:45:19,938 --> 01:45:23,149
Find out who he is. What's he like?
Where'd he get that blue suit?

1114
01:45:23,316 --> 01:45:26,486
Did he have it made?
Is it silk? Is it plastic?

1115
01:45:26,694 --> 01:45:30,323
<i>I know it all seems a bit much,
but how else was I going to meet you?</i>

1116
01:45:30,490 --> 01:45:34,994
<i>I knew you'd never accept
an invitation to tea.</i>

1117
01:45:35,703 --> 01:45:41,292
<i>But a disaster, with people in danger,
people who need help...</i>

1118
01:45:41,459 --> 01:45:46,256
<i>...well, I just knew you couldn't resist
the chance to sort of pitch in.</i>

1119
01:45:46,422 --> 01:45:48,216
<i>Know What I mean?</i>

1120
01:46:05,775 --> 01:46:07,235
It's Superman.

1121
01:46:17,245 --> 01:46:18,955
GIRL 1: Look.
GIRL 2: Oh, my God!

1122
01:46:21,040 --> 01:46:25,044
LEX: <i>There's</i> a <i>strong streak of good
in you, Superman...</i>

1123
01:46:25,378 --> 01:46:28,047
<i>...but then, nobody's perfect.</i>

1124
01:46:30,341 --> 01:46:32,343
<i>Almost nobody.</i>

1125
01:46:40,059 --> 01:46:41,895
- What the--?
- Oh, Superman.

1126
01:46:42,061 --> 01:46:44,314
- Gee.
- Stand back, please. Stand back.

1127
01:46:44,480 --> 01:46:46,274
Nothing to get worried about.

1128
01:46:52,071 --> 01:46:53,781
Well, don't just sit there. Get out.

1129
01:46:53,990 --> 01:46:55,658
I think he's coming, Mr. Luthor.

1130
01:47:12,300 --> 01:47:13,885
[CREAKING]

1131
01:47:14,928 --> 01:47:17,221
He's definitely coming, Mr. Luthor.

1132
01:47:28,816 --> 01:47:30,610
It's open. Come in.

1133
01:47:32,612 --> 01:47:35,907
My attorney will be in touch with you
about the damage to the door.

1134
01:47:36,074 --> 01:47:37,951
Otis, take the gentleman's cape.

1135
01:47:43,539 --> 01:47:47,126
- I don't think he wants me to, Mr. Luthor.
- Luthor, where's the gas pellet?

1136
01:47:47,627 --> 01:47:49,045
Somewhere...

1137
01:47:50,838 --> 01:47:55,718
...in the back of my mind, actually.
It's a little idea I was toying with.

1138
01:47:55,885 --> 01:48:00,098
Is that how your warped brain gets its
kicks? Planning the death of innocents?

1139
01:48:00,848 --> 01:48:03,977
No, by causing the death
of innocent people.

1140
01:48:04,143 --> 01:48:05,728
MAN [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Fire.</i>

1141
01:48:07,647 --> 01:48:10,817
<i>Navy Bird, we have a launch.</i>

1142
01:48:10,984 --> 01:48:14,404
<i>Navy missile, XK 101</i>.

1143
01:48:14,570 --> 01:48:15,989
<i>Angle of attack is perfect.</i>

1144
01:48:16,990 --> 01:48:20,326
<i>- Climbing fast.
MAN 2: Hydraulics, general function.</i>

1145
01:48:20,493 --> 01:48:24,580
LEX: Now, as you may or may not know,
I am, as they say...

1146
01:48:24,747 --> 01:48:27,166
...very heavy into real estate.

1147
01:48:27,375 --> 01:48:31,754
To make money in that game, you have to buy
for a little and sell for a lot, right?

1148
01:48:31,921 --> 01:48:34,257
- Right.
- Right.

1149
01:48:34,424 --> 01:48:37,176
So the problem:

1150
01:48:37,385 --> 01:48:40,179
How to make land more valuable
between the time you buy it...

1151
01:48:40,388 --> 01:48:42,390
...and the time you sell it.

1152
01:48:42,765 --> 01:48:47,437
Now, this is California, the richest,
most populous state in the union.

1153
01:48:47,603 --> 01:48:50,690
I don't need a geography lesson
from you, Luthor.

1154
01:48:50,898 --> 01:48:55,111
Oh, yes, of course, you've been there.
I do forget, you get around, don't you?

1155
01:48:55,278 --> 01:48:57,447
- Where was I?
- California.

1156
01:48:57,613 --> 01:49:01,117
California, right. The San Andreas Fault.
Maybe you've heard of it?

1157
01:49:01,284 --> 01:49:05,038
Yes. It's the joining of two land masses.
The fault line is unstable...

1158
01:49:05,204 --> 01:49:07,832
...which is why you get earthquakes
in California.

1159
01:49:07,999 --> 01:49:10,918
Wonderful.
Couldn't have said it better myself.

1160
01:49:11,127 --> 01:49:15,465
Everything west of this line
is the richest real estate in the world.

1161
01:49:15,631 --> 01:49:18,301
San Diego, Los Angeles, San Francisco.

1162
01:49:18,468 --> 01:49:23,222
Everything on this side is just hundreds
of miles of worthless desert land...

1163
01:49:23,431 --> 01:49:24,974
...which happens to be owned by...

1164
01:49:25,141 --> 01:49:26,184
[THWACK]

1165
01:49:26,350 --> 01:49:28,978
Lex Luthor, Incorporated.

1166
01:49:29,187 --> 01:49:33,566
Now, call me foolish,
call me irresponsible...

1167
01:49:33,733 --> 01:49:37,028
It occurs to me
that a 500-megaton bomb...

1168
01:49:37,195 --> 01:49:40,031
...planted at just the proper point,
would...

1169
01:49:40,198 --> 01:49:42,575
Would destroy most of California.

1170
01:49:43,701 --> 01:49:47,163
Millions of innocent people would die.
The West Coast as we know it would--

1171
01:49:47,330 --> 01:49:51,667
Fall into the sea. Bye-bye, California.

1172
01:49:51,834 --> 01:49:55,046
Hello, new West Coast.
My West Coast.

1173
01:49:57,465 --> 01:50:00,968
Costa del Lex, Luthorville,
Marina del Lex, Otisburg--

1174
01:50:03,846 --> 01:50:06,265
- Otisburg?
- Miss Teschmacher...

1175
01:50:06,474 --> 01:50:08,768
- ...she's got her own place, Mr.--
- Otisburg?

1176
01:50:08,976 --> 01:50:11,938
- It's a little-bitty place.
- Otisburg?

1177
01:50:12,105 --> 01:50:15,108
Okay. I'll just wipe it off, that's all.
It's a little town.

1178
01:50:15,274 --> 01:50:18,528
You're a dreamer, Lex Luthor.
A sick, twisted dreamer.

1179
01:50:18,694 --> 01:50:20,947
Your plan couldn't possibly work.

1180
01:50:21,114 --> 01:50:26,202
I'll admit there were a few problems.
Adjusting the trajectory of the missile...

1181
01:50:26,369 --> 01:50:30,081
...finding the optimum stress point
for the fault line itself.

1182
01:50:30,248 --> 01:50:34,001
Which, by the way,
is target zero, right...

1183
01:50:34,585 --> 01:50:35,628
...here.

1184
01:50:35,795 --> 01:50:37,046
Ooh.

1185
01:50:44,262 --> 01:50:45,721
[HUMMING]

1186
01:51:00,736 --> 01:51:02,029
[CHATTERING]

1187
01:51:05,283 --> 01:51:08,161
- What's happening, lieutenant?
- Trajectory malfunction, sir.

1188
01:51:10,454 --> 01:51:13,166
- Then abort.
- Yes, sir.

1189
01:51:18,754 --> 01:51:20,006
Function negative, sir.

1190
01:51:20,173 --> 01:51:23,009
- Can't you knock them down?
- Absolutely impossible, sir.

1191
01:51:23,176 --> 01:51:25,845
They have the new B-20 low-level
avoidance systems.

1192
01:51:26,053 --> 01:51:27,763
Get me the Pentagon.

1193
01:51:34,103 --> 01:51:37,690
Well, what do you think, Supe baby?
Interesting?

1194
01:51:37,857 --> 01:51:42,445
- Your theory's quite impressive, Luthor.
- Otis, would you go to the viewing room?

1195
01:51:43,112 --> 01:51:46,032
But as for the rest,
it's nothing but a sick fantasy.

1196
01:51:46,199 --> 01:51:49,202
Fantasy? No. No.

1197
01:51:49,368 --> 01:51:52,371
It's history. It's happening, Superman.

1198
01:51:52,580 --> 01:51:54,207
Miss Teschmacher!

1199
01:51:58,878 --> 01:52:01,964
- Yes, Lex?
- Where's the rocket now?

1200
01:52:02,131 --> 01:52:05,885
It's going like a bat over the
Grand Canyon. So is the other one.

1201
01:52:06,093 --> 01:52:09,096
The other one? There's two of them?

1202
01:52:11,599 --> 01:52:14,560
Yeah, Superman. Double jeopardy.

1203
01:52:14,727 --> 01:52:17,688
Even you, with your great speed,
couldn't stop both of them.

1204
01:52:17,855 --> 01:52:21,359
While I, on the other hand,
could stop them with my detonator.

1205
01:52:21,525 --> 01:52:25,112
All right, Luthor. Where is it?
Where's the detonator?

1206
01:52:27,240 --> 01:52:28,741
[GRUNTS]

1207
01:52:38,918 --> 01:52:40,503
You diseased maniac.

1208
01:52:40,670 --> 01:52:43,881
Did you really think you could hide it
from me by encasing it in lead?

1209
01:52:44,048 --> 01:52:45,508
[GRUNTS]

1210
01:52:45,925 --> 01:52:49,929
- I'll mold this box into your prison bars.
- Don't touch that.

1211
01:52:56,519 --> 01:53:01,774
I told you. It's kryptonite, Superman.
A little souvenir from the old hometown.

1212
01:53:02,191 --> 01:53:05,278
I've spared no expense
to make you feel right at home.

1213
01:53:12,243 --> 01:53:16,872
You were great in your day, Superman.
But it just stands to reason...

1214
01:53:17,039 --> 01:53:19,250
...when it came time
to cash in your chips...

1215
01:53:19,417 --> 01:53:23,087
...this old, diseased maniac...

1216
01:53:23,254 --> 01:53:25,423
...would be your banker.

1217
01:53:28,551 --> 01:53:30,720
Mind over muscle.

1218
01:53:36,058 --> 01:53:37,310
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

1219
01:53:38,227 --> 01:53:42,898
You don't even care where
the other missile's headed, do you?

1220
01:53:43,065 --> 01:53:47,486
Certainly, I do.
I know exactly where it's headed.

1221
01:53:47,695 --> 01:53:49,322
Hackensack, New Jersey.

1222
01:53:49,697 --> 01:53:51,574
[MOANS]

1223
01:53:55,202 --> 01:53:57,913
I have to leave you now.
No hard feelings.

1224
01:53:58,080 --> 01:54:02,084
We all have our little faults.
Mine's in California.

1225
01:54:16,349 --> 01:54:20,353
Lex, my mother lives in Hackensack.

1226
01:54:30,237 --> 01:54:32,740
Miss Teschmacher!

1227
01:54:50,883 --> 01:54:52,551
<i>MAN</i> [OVER RADIO]: <i>Both birds uncontrolled.</i>

1228
01:54:52,760 --> 01:54:54,011
<i>Impossible to reset.</i>

1229
01:55:00,184 --> 01:55:01,644
LEX:
Otis.

1230
01:55:06,524 --> 01:55:08,317
[GASPS]

1231
01:55:20,162 --> 01:55:22,164
Miss Teschmacher.

1232
01:55:22,331 --> 01:55:24,291
Miss Teschmacher.

1233
01:55:25,918 --> 01:55:28,504
Please, you can't...

1234
01:55:28,671 --> 01:55:30,005
You can't just stand there.

1235
01:55:30,172 --> 01:55:32,174
Shh.

1236
01:55:33,551 --> 01:55:35,052
You can't just stand there...

1237
01:55:35,219 --> 01:55:38,055
...and let innocent people,
millions of innocent people, die.

1238
01:55:39,056 --> 01:55:40,808
Maybe.

1239
01:55:41,725 --> 01:55:44,228
Please. Please help me to save them.

1240
01:55:46,313 --> 01:55:48,816
If I help you, do you promise
to save my mother first?

1241
01:55:50,025 --> 01:55:52,069
But Lois and Jimmy...

1242
01:55:52,236 --> 01:55:53,612
Oh, but my mother comes first.

1243
01:55:53,821 --> 01:55:57,324
If you promise me, I'll believe you,
because you always tell the truth.

1244
01:55:59,618 --> 01:56:02,329
I promise. I promise.

1245
01:56:56,675 --> 01:56:59,261
Why did you kiss me first?

1246
01:57:00,387 --> 01:57:03,641
It-- I didn't think you'd let me later.

1247
01:57:04,642 --> 01:57:06,602
Thank you, Miss Teschmacher.

1248
01:57:06,769 --> 01:57:10,814
Why is it I can't get it on
with the good guys?

1249
01:57:15,778 --> 01:57:17,154
Stand aside, now.

1250
01:57:17,321 --> 01:57:18,989
I wouldn't stay here, either.

1251
01:57:37,550 --> 01:57:39,218
<i>MAN:
Army bird still heading due east.</i>

1252
01:57:39,426 --> 01:57:42,846
<i>- Navy bird still heading due west.
MAN 2: Losing radar contact.</i>

1253
01:57:43,013 --> 01:57:45,057
<i>Next radar contact in 3 seconds.</i>

1254
01:57:45,307 --> 01:57:46,976
<i>--Intercept both birds.</i>

1255
01:58:06,579 --> 01:58:08,706
Army bird still headed east, sir.

1256
01:58:57,546 --> 01:58:59,548
[BEEPING]

1257
01:59:03,594 --> 01:59:05,929
MAN: <i>Army bird gaining altitude.</i>
- Miss Teschmacher.

1258
01:59:06,096 --> 01:59:09,141
<i>MAN 2: Radar contact strong.
- We have straight climb.</i>

1259
01:59:09,308 --> 01:59:11,310
Miss Teschmacher!

1260
01:59:11,518 --> 01:59:13,812
MAN: <i>Radar report,
Navy bird, San Andreas area.</i>

1261
01:59:14,021 --> 01:59:16,398
<i>Heading down.
Fifteen seconds to impact.</i>

1262
01:59:16,565 --> 01:59:19,026
<i>Navy bird heading down,
15 seconds to impact.</i>

1263
01:59:19,568 --> 01:59:21,111
<i>Fifteen seconds and counting.</i>

1264
01:59:23,072 --> 01:59:26,158
[SUPERTRAMPS' "GIVE A LITTLE BIT"
PLAYS OVER RADIO]

1265
01:59:30,120 --> 01:59:32,039
[HONKING]

1266
01:59:38,671 --> 01:59:40,756
MAN: <i>Impact: San Andreas.</i>
- God!

1267
02:00:00,109 --> 02:00:01,151
[GLASS SHATTERING]

1268
02:00:09,118 --> 02:00:10,953
Oh.

1269
02:00:11,620 --> 02:00:12,788
[GASPS]

1270
02:00:17,584 --> 02:00:19,503
NEWSMAN <i>[ON</i> RADIO]:
<i>We interrupt the program for</i> a <i>newsflash.</i>

1271
02:00:19,670 --> 02:00:23,006
<i>A military missile has exploded
in the Southern California desert.</i>

1272
02:00:23,173 --> 02:00:26,552
<i>The force of the explosion
has activated the San Andreas Fault.</i>

1273
02:00:26,719 --> 02:00:29,388
<i>California is suffering
a major earthquake.</i>

1274
02:00:36,520 --> 02:00:37,730
[CREAKING]

1275
02:00:38,897 --> 02:00:40,482
[CARS HONKING]

1276
02:00:42,317 --> 02:00:44,111
[SCREAMING]

1277
02:00:47,030 --> 02:00:48,323
[BAAING]

1278
02:00:50,117 --> 02:00:51,660
Ah!

1279
02:00:52,035 --> 02:00:53,912
MAN 1:
What's going on?

1280
02:00:55,706 --> 02:00:56,832
MAN 2:
It's a quake. Look!

1281
02:00:59,126 --> 02:01:00,711
[CHATTERING AND SCREAMING]

1282
02:01:08,010 --> 02:01:09,011
[TIRES SCREECHING]

1283
02:01:10,846 --> 02:01:12,139
TEEN:
Look out!

1284
02:01:20,522 --> 02:01:22,399
[CREAKING]

1285
02:01:23,025 --> 02:01:24,693
DRIVER:
Get to the back of the bus!

1286
02:01:49,384 --> 02:01:50,427
[SCREAMING]

1287
02:02:05,108 --> 02:02:06,777
SUPERMAN:
Okay, kids. It's all right now.

1288
02:02:06,944 --> 02:02:08,612
GIRL:
Thank God, we're back on the bridge.

1289
02:02:08,779 --> 02:02:11,240
- Hey, it's Superman.
TEEN: It's Superman!

1290
02:02:18,205 --> 02:02:20,290
Holy mackerel!

1291
02:02:21,250 --> 02:02:22,334
MAN:
Going off the tracks!

1292
02:02:24,962 --> 02:02:26,338
Hang on!

1293
02:02:30,092 --> 02:02:31,218
I can't hold her!

1294
02:02:32,261 --> 02:02:33,762
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

1295
02:02:43,856 --> 02:02:45,482
[RUMBLING]

1296
02:02:51,154 --> 02:02:52,781
[ALARM WAILS]

1297
02:02:58,787 --> 02:03:00,622
<i>MAN</i> [OVER PA]: <i>All
personnel, evacuate the dam.</i>

1298
02:03:00,789 --> 02:03:02,499
<i>All personnel, evacuate the dam.</i>

1299
02:03:03,166 --> 02:03:04,626
Ah!

1300
02:03:12,467 --> 02:03:14,177
WORKER 1:
Watch that cable!

1301
02:03:14,344 --> 02:03:15,888
My eyes! I can't see!

1302
02:03:21,518 --> 02:03:23,228
WORKER 2:
Someone try and pull the main!

1303
02:03:23,395 --> 02:03:25,647
WORKER 3:
It's impossible, it's red-hot!

1304
02:03:25,814 --> 02:03:27,649
[SCREAMING]

1305
02:03:32,654 --> 02:03:33,906
[MAIN POWERS DOWN]

1306
02:03:34,072 --> 02:03:36,491
- Gentlemen, is that man all right?
- Yeah.

1307
02:03:59,681 --> 02:04:02,517
- Ah--!
- Hang on, Jim.

1308
02:04:12,235 --> 02:04:13,528
MAN:
The dam burst!

1309
02:04:13,862 --> 02:04:16,949
Forget the car! Come on, come on!

1310
02:04:21,203 --> 02:04:23,205
You're safe here, son.

1311
02:04:24,373 --> 02:04:26,541
That's okay!
Miss Lane will be driving by soon.

1312
02:04:36,385 --> 02:04:38,387
- Come on, George.
MAN: Make for the hill.

1313
02:04:38,595 --> 02:04:40,055
[RUMBLING]

1314
02:04:45,394 --> 02:04:48,647
<i>MAN</i> [OVER RADIO]: <i>There's been major
quake damage to Southern California.</i>

1315
02:04:48,855 --> 02:04:51,400
<i>The San Andreas Fault
has miraculously sealed itself...</i>

1316
02:04:51,566 --> 02:04:56,071
<i>...yet Southern California is suffering
major aftershocks of a major earthquake.</i>

1317
02:04:56,238 --> 02:04:58,240
<i>The population is warned
to be aware of...</i>

1318
02:05:00,450 --> 02:05:01,743
Please, come on, turn over.

1319
02:05:01,910 --> 02:05:03,787
<i>- ...which in some areas has-
- Come on'.!</i>

1320
02:05:06,456 --> 02:05:08,166
[GASPS]

1321
02:05:08,417 --> 02:05:09,876
[SCREAMING]

1322
02:05:24,391 --> 02:05:26,309
[SCREAMING AND GROANING]

1323
02:05:31,440 --> 02:05:33,275
Help me. Help me.

1324
02:05:38,447 --> 02:05:40,490
[SCREAMING]

1325
02:06:44,096 --> 02:06:45,847
[GRUNTING]

1326
02:06:51,019 --> 02:06:52,687
[COUGHING]

1327
02:07:25,011 --> 02:07:26,054
[COUGHING]

1328
02:07:27,722 --> 02:07:28,765
[MOUTHS]
<i>Lois.</i>

1329
02:07:33,812 --> 02:07:35,397
[MOANING]

1330
02:10:21,688 --> 02:10:23,732
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

1331
02:10:24,733 --> 02:10:27,736
No, no, no....

1332
02:10:28,737 --> 02:10:31,573
No...

1333
02:10:31,740 --> 02:10:36,328
[SCREAMS]

1334
02:10:42,917 --> 02:10:44,252
[THUNDER CRASHES]

1335
02:10:44,419 --> 02:10:46,338
<i>My son.</i>

1336
02:10:46,588 --> 02:10:49,591
<i>It is forbidden for you to interfere
in human history.</i>

1337
02:10:49,758 --> 02:10:54,971
JONATHAN: <i>One thing I do know, son,
and that is you are here for a reason.</i>

1338
02:10:55,138 --> 02:10:58,266
JOR-EL: <i>It is forbidden for you to...</i>
CLARK: <i>Those things I can do...</i>

1339
02:10:58,433 --> 02:11:01,770
<i>...all those powers,
and I couldn't even save him.</i>

1340
02:11:01,936 --> 02:11:03,605
<i>It is forbidden.</i>

1341
02:11:05,982 --> 02:11:08,234
<i>It is forbidden.</i>

1342
02:12:10,922 --> 02:12:12,674
[ENGINE WON'T START]

1343
02:12:33,194 --> 02:12:34,612
Hi-

1344
02:12:36,030 --> 02:12:37,449
Don't bother, I think it's dead.

1345
02:12:39,367 --> 02:12:41,411
Sure it's dead.

1346
02:12:42,537 --> 02:12:45,957
The problem with Men of Steel, there's
never one around when you want one.

1347
02:12:46,124 --> 02:12:48,460
Know what happened to me
while you were off flying?

1348
02:12:48,626 --> 02:12:50,211
I was almost in an earthquake...

1349
02:12:50,378 --> 02:12:52,380
...I had this gas station blow up...

1350
02:12:52,547 --> 02:12:54,883
...there's telephone poles
falling all over...

1351
02:12:55,049 --> 02:12:57,886
...I'm almost killed,
and to top the whole thing off...

1352
02:12:58,052 --> 02:12:59,637
...this stupid car runs out of gas!

1353
02:12:59,846 --> 02:13:01,723
I'm sorry about that, Lois...

1354
02:13:01,890 --> 02:13:04,058
...but I've been kind of busy for a while.

1355
02:13:06,603 --> 02:13:09,063
I'm sorry. That's all right.

1356
02:13:18,781 --> 02:13:20,366
JIMMY
Hey!

1357
02:13:20,909 --> 02:13:22,160
Thanks a lot, Superman.

1358
02:13:22,577 --> 02:13:25,163
You put me in the middle of nowhere
during an earthquake.

1359
02:13:25,371 --> 02:13:27,415
No food, no water, snakes everywhere.

1360
02:13:27,582 --> 02:13:30,251
- I had no idea if you were coming back--
BOTH: Jimmy.

1361
02:13:30,418 --> 02:13:31,419
[MUFFLED SPEAKING]

1362
02:13:31,586 --> 02:13:34,923
Listen, there's something I have to do.
I'll see you later.

1363
02:13:37,258 --> 02:13:39,677
He can't stay still for a second.

1364
02:13:40,803 --> 02:13:42,931
Oh. Golly, Miss Lane...

1365
02:13:43,097 --> 02:13:45,141
...it's too bad
Mr. Kent didn't see all this.

1366
02:13:45,308 --> 02:13:46,809
Yeah, poor Clark.

1367
02:13:46,976 --> 02:13:48,978
He's never around when S--

1368
02:13:49,395 --> 02:13:50,772
Clark-- Wait a minute.

1369
02:13:50,939 --> 02:13:52,690
- Wait a minute.
- What?

1370
02:13:54,275 --> 02:13:56,486
Lois Lane, that is the silliest idea ever.

1371
02:13:56,653 --> 02:14:00,448
Let me tell you something, Miss Lane,
I think he really cares about you.

1372
02:14:00,615 --> 02:14:02,659
- Clark? Of course he does.
- No, not Clark.

1373
02:14:05,286 --> 02:14:09,832
Oh, well, Superman cares
about everybody, Jimmy.

1374
02:14:10,291 --> 02:14:14,629
<i>But, who knows, someday,
you know, if he's lucky...</i>

1375
02:14:21,135 --> 02:14:23,304
[ALARM WAILING]

1376
02:14:23,471 --> 02:14:25,181
[DOGS BARKING]

1377
02:14:26,933 --> 02:14:28,518
You're messing up my suit.

1378
02:14:28,685 --> 02:14:30,478
You big lummox, you.

1379
02:14:30,645 --> 02:14:32,689
Come on, stop it, will you?

1380
02:14:32,855 --> 02:14:35,483
Otis, it's your fault.
Watch the ground!

1381
02:14:36,192 --> 02:14:37,527
Good evening, warden.

1382
02:14:37,694 --> 02:14:39,487
These two men should be safe here...

1383
02:14:39,654 --> 02:14:42,031
- ...until they can get a fair trial.
- Who is it?

1384
02:14:44,492 --> 02:14:46,035
Lex Luthor!

1385
02:14:46,202 --> 02:14:48,997
- The greatest criminal mind of our time!
- Of our time!

1386
02:14:49,163 --> 02:14:50,707
- I hereby serve notice...
- Notice.

1387
02:14:50,957 --> 02:14:52,667
...that these walls--
- These walls here...

1388
02:14:52,834 --> 02:14:54,002
Will you shut up, please?

1389
02:14:54,168 --> 02:14:55,670
All right, take them away, boys.

1390
02:14:55,837 --> 02:14:58,214
- You nitwit. Nincompoop!
OTIS: Guard, guard...

1391
02:14:58,381 --> 02:15:02,510
This country is safe again, Superman,
thanks to you.

1392
02:15:02,677 --> 02:15:04,679
No, sir. Don't thank me, warden.

1393
02:15:05,346 --> 02:15:07,515
We're all part of the same team.

1394
02:15:07,682 --> 02:15:09,183
Night.

1395
02:22:57,151 --> 02:22:59,153
[English - US - SDH]

